1
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,400
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,680
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:40,080
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,640
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,240 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,520
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 9]

23
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:37,840
[Binhai Customs Training Center]

24
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,660
Dress center, dress!

25
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:51,220
Right, dress!

26
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,540
Persistence wins!

27
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,860
We have to reach the finish

28
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,260
before sunrise!

29
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,340
It's only five kilometers,

30
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:04,180
and half of you

31
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:05,340
are already down!

32
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:06,700
You 20-somethings

33
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:09,610
can't outdo a 40-year-old like me?

34
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:10,610
Come on!

35
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,740
In the future,

36
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,420
you'll be guarding the border!

37
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,260
Come on!

38
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,500
Come on!

39
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:17,940
Keep up!

40
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:22,540
Hustle!

41
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,780
Hustle!

42
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:30,660
Stay strong!

43
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:31,780
Keep it up!

44
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:32,860
Hang in there!

45
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:33,500
Zhang Dayu!

46
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,020
Over here!

47
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,140
Mr. Chen, water.

48
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,100
What water?

49
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:39,900
Doing what?

50
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:40,660
I…

51
00:02:41,160 --> 00:02:41,300
I…

52
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:42,260
I'm just cheering them on.

53
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,380
Cheering what?

54
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:43,980
They're training,

55
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:44,660
and you?

56
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,300
I…

57
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:45,740
Well…

58
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:47,100
I can't help it!

59
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:47,940
They won't take me!

60
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,740
Why not?

61
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,260
Guess I'm too chunky.

62
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:51,820
But I've lost three kilos lately!

63
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,180
Who said that?

64
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,140
My roommates.

65
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,660
Guo Cong, Shihuo,

66
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:57,540
and…

67
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:58,260
Wang Wenlei.

68
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:03,660
Assemble!

69
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,420
Assemble!

70
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,780
Left turn!

71
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:06,620
Double-time!

72
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,140
Right, dress!

73
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,900
- Attention! - Fall in!

74
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,060
Eyes front!

75
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:21,860
From now on,

76
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,380
we move from two-man teams

77
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:25,020
to four-man teams.

78
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:26,340
Guo Cong!

79
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:26,740
Here!

80
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,140
Jiang Shihuo!

81
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:28,500
Here!

82
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:29,780
Wang Wenlei!

83
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,180
Here!

84
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:32,500
Zhang Dayu!

85
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:33,140
Here!

86
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,100
Step out!

87
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,140
You've trained this before.

88
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,020
Ready!

89
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:38,540
Yes!

90
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,460
Come on!

91
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,220
Come on!

92
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:44,900
Teamwork

93
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,100
starts with

94
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,780
mutual trust.

95
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,140
Then,

96
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:52,100
you cover what others lack.

97
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,100
In our team,

98
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,540
we've got all kinds!

99
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,020
So,

100
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:58,420
you need

101
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,660
to cover each other's weaknesses,

102
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:02,220
and also

103
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,980
have the guts to share consequences!

104
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:06,940
Got it?

105
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,100
Got it!

106
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,180
You four, get up!

107
00:04:10,600 --> 00:04:10,980
Fall in!

108
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:20,300
All!

109
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,490
Right turn!

110
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:23,420
Five kilometers!

111
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,300
Double-time!

112
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,740
Isn't this a bit much?

113
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,220
Like I said,

114
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:38,220
no pain, no gain.

115
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:46,080
[Trainee File
Name: Jiang Shihuo]

116
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:49,280
[Trainee File
Name: Zhang Dayu]

117
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:59,760
[Trainee File
Name: Guo Cong]

118
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:19,680
[Emergency Contact
Xiang Xiuyuan]

119
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,500
Need help?

120
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,940
Go out!

121
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,160
Too much smoke here!

122
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,400
The fire's strong, stay back!

123
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,080
I'm fine!

124
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:40,280
Here.

125
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:44,160
It's slippery right here.

126
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,920
Been waiting for you to come order.

127
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,160
Not even a holiday.

128
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:49,440
Why'd you hit me up?

129
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,160
Things that slow at airport customs now?

130
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:54,440
Lately, I'm not at the airport.

131
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,200
I got reassigned

132
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:58,920
to run the Customs rookie training.

133
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:01,480
So this is about Cong?

134
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,640
I like keeping smart company like you.

135
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:10,720
He listed you as his emergency contact.

136
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,360
Makes sense.

137
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,800
I did his parents meetings
when he was in junior high.

138
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:16,980
Hold on,

139
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,860
what exactly are you two?

140
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:20,020
You're overthinking it.

141
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:20,540
It's not like that.

142
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,220
You know me.

143
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:23,980
Back in 2004,

144
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,020
I left the system

145
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,460
and started this company.

146
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,500
My partner back then

147
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,780
was Cong's dad.

148
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,340
His name was Guo Shuliang,

149
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,420
he also went to UIBE,

150
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,660
three years ahead.

151
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:35,740
Doesn't ring a bell?

152
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,500
Tall guy, good-looking.

153
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,140
We were both in the drama club.

154
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,180
Yeah, that rings a bell.

155
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,260
Around 2008,

156
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,500
we were out at sea delivering goods,

157
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:49,380
ran into heavy winds.

158
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,860
Shuliang fell overboard…

159
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,420
and didn't make it.

160
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:56,460
And then?

161
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:00,740
Then…

162
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:06,100
Cong was only 15 or 16,

163
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,420
just a kid.

164
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,940
I couldn't just leave him on his own.

165
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,460
Besides

166
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:12,780
helping him financially,

167
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,900
I tried to do

168
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,540
what his father would've done.

169
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:18,460
Got it.

170
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,180
How's the kid?

171
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,340
With your sharp eye,

172
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,020
you're asking me?

173
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,260
I'd say,

174
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:31,380
he's got pride,

175
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,220
he's driven,

176
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,660
and

177
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,740
pretty stubborn.

178
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,740
Yeah, stubborn,

179
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,620
just like his dad.

180
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,300
He was pretty lost for a while

181
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:42,820
back in school.

182
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,660
Then he took advice from his mom and me,

183
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,100
got into our university, UIBE.

184
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,540
Originally, I figured

185
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,140
after four years,

186
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,100
he'd either go abroad for further study

187
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,180
or take over what his dad

188
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:54,980
and I built.

189
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,500
But this kid

190
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,300
didn't want either path.

191
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,900
He took the Customs exam instead.

192
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,620
And he actually passed.

193
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:04,780
Only told me after.

194
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,660
He's got his own head now.

195
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,180
You know,

196
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:08,140
Cong knows

197
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,100
absolutely nothing

198
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,460
about Customs.

199
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,980
Now that you've got him,

200
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,980
make him back off.

201
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,140
Come on!

202
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,580
What do you take Customs for?

203
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,180
Come and go

204
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,100
as you please, huh?

205
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:23,820
Sanhe, you know me.

206
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:25,980
My wife already moved abroad,

207
00:08:26,840 --> 00:08:28,420
and I'm basically on my own now.

208
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:29,340
Right?

209
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,060
I've watched Cong grow up.

210
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:32,740
He's like half a son to me.

211
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,340
I think

212
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,420
he hasn't really figured out

213
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,460
what he wants.

214
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:39,060
He just drifted into Customs.

215
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:40,300
Do me a favor,

216
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:42,650
have him take over the company.

217
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,180
Then his four years of trade studies

218
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,020
won't go to waste.

219
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:48,100
As for me,

220
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:50,460
I don't care how
he got into this line of work.

221
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,620
But when I look into his eyes,

222
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:56,460
I see confidence
and real interest in Customs.

223
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,540
You that sure

224
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,180
you're not wrong?

225
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:58,900
Of course.

226
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,260
I think

227
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:02,140
he's got potential.

228
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,860
With everything I know about him,

229
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:07,420
I'd say he might not
actually be suited for it.

230
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,660
He looks stubborn,

231
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,380
but he's quite fragile inside.

232
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,660
I'm worried

233
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,420
that if he gives up halfway,

234
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:15,620
it'll ruin him.

235
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,500
You're reaching.

236
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,140
If he's not cut out for it,

237
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,900
I'd return him

238
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,700
before he could even bail.

239
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,180
That's perfect.

240
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,180
Just send him back,

241
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:26,740
I'll take him.

242
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:29,220
Just don't wanna see
you get let down, old pal.

243
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,460
Sanhe!

244
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,820
Slow down!

245
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,620
Stop! Listen!

246
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:46,980
Guo Cong's in trouble!

247
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:48,140
What?

248
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,140
Cops rang, gotta go pick him up.

249
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,480
[Binhai City PSB
Chengnan Police Station]

250
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,140
Officer, hello.

251
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:10,460
I'm his supervisor.

252
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,180
What happened?

253
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,380
Just a misunderstanding.

254
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,340
Sorry you had to come.

255
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:13,900
It's fine.

256
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,940
This concerns the honor of our Customs.

257
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:16,700
Talking about that,

258
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,860
we'll send Customs

259
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,220
a formal letter of appreciation

260
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,580
to thank Mr. Guo Cong

261
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,620
for helping us apprehend

262
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,260
a child trafficking suspect.

263
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,940
Well, the letter won't be necessary.

264
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,940
He's a customs trainee.

265
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,460
Just doing his job.

266
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,780
He saved a kidnapped child.

267
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,100
That's saving a family.

268
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,140
All stick, no carrot?
Not Customs style.

269
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,140
Exactly.

270
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,420
Merit should be recognized.

271
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,700
The letter is necessary.

272
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:40,620
Alright, thanks.

273
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,180
Good.

274
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:41,980
Young lad,

275
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,420
good job,

276
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,060
keep it up.

277
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,260
All thanks to Mr. Chen.

278
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,620
So you ended up in the police station?

279
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:49,580
Alright, I'll get him back.

280
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,220
Okay.

281
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:50,820
Thank you.

282
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,260
Nothing.

283
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,460
- Thanks. - Thanks.

284
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:52,820
Bye.

285
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:57,220
[Chengnan Police Station]
Why are you here?

286
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,140
[Chengnan Police Station]
What took you so long?

287
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,380
[Chengnan Police Station]
Wanna take it there?

288
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:00,420
[Chengnan Police Station]
I'm his uncle.

289
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:01,740
[Chengnan Police Station]
He called me, of course I came.

290
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,980
[Chengnan Police Station]
You two know each other?

291
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,940
Know each other?

292
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,340
We were college classmates.

293
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,500
UIBE,

294
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,220
you too?

295
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,540
Wow. Great observation.

